item.title: Import problem
item.dc:creator: @eczema3 eczema3
item.description:
@eczema3 wrote:

I saw in someone’s Java code they had imported i think it was 5 themes into what they were making by doing this

import theme.BlackTheme; import theme.OrangeTheme; import theme.GreenTheme; import theme.RedTheme; import theme.BlackWTheme;

I wanted to use these themes, to improve the looks of what i am making. But when i went to compile i got these erors:

CapitalizeMe.java:14: package theme does not exist import theme.BlackTheme; ^ CapitalizeMe.java:15: package theme does not exist import theme.OrangeTheme; ^ CapitalizeMe.java:16: package theme does not exist import theme.GreenTheme; ^ CapitalizeMe.java:17: package theme does not exist import theme.RedTheme; ^ CapitalizeMe.java:18: package theme does not exist import theme.BlackWTheme; ^ 5 errors Press any key to continue . . .

Can anyone understand why?
